steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bdomp","text":"Use our Excel template ( ) to copy existing 16S/18S/ITS primers or to design your own custom gene primers with the proper Illumina indices and Nextera adapter orientations. We order IDT “Ultramers” for such long primers (~80-90 nt) as their coupling efficiency is one of the highest available (critical for obtaining high proportions of full-length oligos in the mix you obtain). {"blocks":[{"key":"bg32a","text":"Once arrived, do a short spin of the plate in case lyophilized material was dislodged, then add   of PCR-grade water to each well containing the primers in order to reconstitute them at a concentration of   (1/10th the typical 100 µM working stock concentration for primers). Mix well by pipetting up and down at least 3 times and seal the plate with Bio-Rad film. Alternatively, the plate is sealed with Bio-Rad film and mixed well by vortexing it on a benchtop vortex for   and then doing a short spin at approx.  . We have found that these primers usually need a significant incubation time for the lyophilized pellets to re-suspend well – we typically leave them overnight at   before continuing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":96,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":205,"length":1},{"key":2,"offset":474,"length":1},{"key":3,"offset":515,"length":1},{"key":4,"offset":680,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"400","error":false,"guid":"38564D209D0511EC9D44599976141BE3","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":1}},"1":{"type":"concentration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"concentration":"10","error_concentration":false,"guid":"4AFAF2009D0511EC9D44599976141BE3","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":29}},"2":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":30,"guid":"B0D1AE60A17511EC832FDF62423E426C","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"3":{"type":"centrifuge","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"centrifuge":"500","duration":30,"error_centrifuge":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"DF108490A17511EC832FDF62423E426C","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"scientificNotation":{"centrifuge":false,"temperature":false},"start":null,"temperature":"","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":33}},"4":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"0839C7A0A17611EC832FDF62423E426C","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ef611","text":"Prepare the   working stock Forward Set 1 Primer Plate (F1) by pipetting   of PCR-grade water into each well of the 96-well PCR plate from a sterile reservoir. Rotate the deep-well primer plate 90° clockwise and align it so that the 8 occupied wells (= 8 different indices) of row 1 line up with the 8 rows of the new plate. Working by column and keeping the same set of tips, transfer   of reconstituted primer into each well of each column, mixing well by pipetting. Once complete, each column of the resulting plate will have enough primer for two complete 96-well plate PCRs (the Pure+1/10th plates; 12 columns × 4 µL × 2 plates = 96 µL required). {"blocks":[{"key":"8kg0n","text":"Prepare the   working stock Reverse Set 1 Primer Plate (R1) by pipetting   of PCR-grade water into each well of the 96-well PCR plate from a sterile reservoir. Align the deep-well primer plate horizontally (normal orientation) so that the 12 occupied wells (= 12 different indices) of row 5 line up with the 12 columns of the new plate. Working by row and keeping the same set of tips, transfer   of reconstituted primer into each well of each row, mixing well by pipetting.
